│ reproducer, Res (%c1) can be poison due to an out-of-bounds extractelement feeding its icmp. Reassociating then makes the transformation more poisonous than the source. A minimal and   │
│ robust fix is to freeze both operands when neither is provably safe and swapping isn’t possible. I will modify GetNewVectorizedTree to freeze both VectorizedTree and Res in that        │
│ fallback, which prevents new poison without relying on complex pattern checks.                                                                                                           │
